            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I agree it makes more sense inside the `flush` guard. Don't remember why I placed it outside tbh, can reconsider the specific use case if this was ext_ui driven and I run into it again. I do remember wanting to reconsider this anyways but it was merged as experimental and I forgot about it.\r\n\r\nI do wonder if the treesitter highlighter wants to set, `flush == true` then. I think this was an improvement: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/28101#issuecomment-2091057965. Although I suppose there was a reason the highlighter didn't call `:redraw` before...",
