            "body": "> I do wonder if the treesitter highlighter wants to set, `flush == true` then. I think this was an improvement: [#28101 (comment)](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/28101#issuecomment-2091057965).\r\n\r\nHm if I set `flush = true` in the highlighter, then I still get the black flickering from https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/28668 even with this PR.\r\n\r\nPerhaps it is possible to redraw without setting the background to black? That would maybe solve #28667 as well.",
